node.text: Watch from just 2.9 miles away as Falcon 9 climbs to orbit at 9:06am this morning. This was one of the loudest launches I’ve heard, and one of the clearest I’ve seen, in recent memory.

node.title: Video: Falcon 9 launches the fourth Starlink mission

node.text:
Milky Way over a Florida beach last night. ✨

14.5 hours & 600 miles for 30 minutes of shooting underneath some of Florida’s darkest skies before clouds rolled in. Great night to likely cap off the season for me as my schedule ramps up and the core’s visibility decreases.

—

Nikon Z7 II + 14-24mm f/2.8 at 19mm
Two exposures:
120”, f/4, ISO 3200 (tracked with a star tracker)
60”, f4, ISO 12800 (tracker off)

node.text: Got some stick time in the L-39 Albatross jet this weekend with @slickbaum. This was my first time controlling an aircraft. It will not be the last. Amazing experience!

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by John Kraus on August 10, 2021 tagging @hayleyarc, @drsianproctor, @inspiration4, @rookisaacman, and @astrosembro. May be an image of 2 people and people standing.

node.text:
Some more scenes from Inspiration4’s fighter jet training weekend in Bozeman, Montana. An amazing experience.

Callsigns were finally bestowed upon crew during an epic party and naming ceremony. “Leo” for Sian, “Hanks” for Chris, and “Nova” for Hayley. I was even lucky enough to get my own, too — “Snap.” So I guess I can say these photos were snapped by Snap for @inspiration4. 🙂

node.text:
Sunset flight with the L-39 Albatross.

That’s @inspiration4 Mission Specialist @astrosembro in the backseat, piloted by Doug Demko aka Tut. Thanks to John Baum aka Slick for piloting me in the L-39 and getting me in position for great shots — such an honor to fly with some amazing people.

node.text:
The crew of Inspiration4 poses in the crew access arm at Launch Complex 39A this week.

In 46 days they’ll walk across this arm to begin the trip of a lifetime! 🌎🚀🐉
